Fantasy2C
C++ 2D-Multimedia Library
Fantasy2C is an object oriented multimedia library, supported with OpenGL. 
Fantasy2C uses hardware acceleration. 
With additional libraries like DevIL,GLFW or Audiere. 
Let yourself quickly and easily load Images, create window or play music and sound.
In Fantasy2C everything is in there what you need for a 2D game. 

Version: 1.1.1

Version History:

1.1.1
[Bugfix]	zoom_x/y in Plane Class
[Buffix]	src_rect in Plane Class
[Bugfix]	Blt function(Bitmap) Alpha blending 
[ShaderGL]	Add copy constructor and assignment operator with deep copy.
[Sprite]	Add flipped horizontal and flipped vertical Variable
[ShaderGL]	Add getSupported[WGL,GLX,Shader,VBO,...] and getGL[Version,Renderer,Vendor] function
[Basic]		More OpenGL extensions added
[Bugfix]	AudioFile Copy constructor memory leak
[TTFFont]	Add defaultdir Varaible, Default System Font directory

1.1.0
[Basic]		Change #include "..." in #include<Fantasy2C/...>
[New]		Class ShaderGL, load shaderfiles and create ARB handles
[Window]	Remove shader management
[Input]		Add mouse repeat function
[Input]		Add getMouseWheelUp and getMouseWheelDown function
[Input]		Remove singleton pattern
[Window]	Remove singleton pattern
[Bugfix]	Input repeat function

